Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportShifter(25.10)                                      reportShifter(25.10)

Name
       reportShifter  - Reports the level shifters that have been read into or
       defined for the Innovus software

Syntax
       reportShifter

       [-help]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       [-from <powerDomainName>]

       [-to <powerDomainName>]

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       [-highlight]

       Reports the level shifters that have been read into or defined for  the
       Innovus software.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each reportShifter parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man reportShifter.

       -cell  Reports shifters with the specified cell.

              Default: Reports all level shifters.

       -from <powerDomainName>
              Reports  all  the shifter instances connected to the output pins
              of the power domain specified in the -from option.

              Default: Reports all level shifters.

       -highlight
              Highlights placed level shifters.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Reports all instances in an output file.

              Default: The instances will be reported to a default output file
              <designName>.shifter.rpt. A warning message is printed to  indi-
              cate a default output file is created.

       -to <powerDomainName>
              Reports  shifter  instances  connected  to the input pins of the
              power domain specified in the -to option.

              Default: Reports all level shifters.

Related Information
       For more information, see the following topics in the Low Power  Design
       chapter of the User Guide.

              * "Overview"

              * "Power Domain Shutdown and Scaling"

              * "Power Switch Optimization"

